sql:
SELECT payment_id
FROM penalty_payments
WHERE payment_status = 'paid';

external_knowledge:
- "penalty payments" refer to financial penalties imposed on companies for violations of regulations or laws;
- "offense type" can include various violations, such as workplace safety or health violations;
- "agency name" refers to the regulatory body that issued the penalty, such as OSHA (Occupational Safety and Health Administration).

- "Total penalties" refer to the sum of all penalty amounts paid by a company;
- "Average penalties" refer to the mean amount paid per violation;
- "Number of violations" refers to the count of unique violation IDs associated with a company.

- "financial penalty" refers to the amount companies pay as a result of regulatory violations;
- "navigate through the treacherous waters of regulatory compliance" metaphorically represents the challenges companies face in adhering to industry regulations;
- "year by year" indicates that the results are grouped and ordered by the year the violations occurred.
